swig: swig (Simplified Wrapper and Interface Generator)
swig:
swig: SWIG is a software development tool that connects programs written in 
swig: C and C++ with a variety of high-level programming languages. SWIG is 
swig: used with different types of languages including common scripting 
swig: languages such as Perl, PHP, Python, Tcl and Ruby. SWIG is most 
swig: commonly used to create high-level interpreted or compiled programming 
swig: environments, user interfaces, and as a tool for testing and prototyping 
swig: C/C++ software. SWIG can also export its parse tree in the form of 
swig: XML and Lisp s-expressions. 
swig:
